# Syntactic Tagger

The Syntactic Tagger is a part-of-speech tagger that uses a lexicon extracted from an electronic dictionary and a plain text corpus to tag texts.

Apart from tagging the text tokens using syntactic tags based on the EAGLES proposal for Spanish, it also lemmatizes each token, creating a representation of the text as a list of lemmas.

The Syntactic Tagger works for Spanish, as it has taken the information from the Diccionario de la Real Academia EspaÃ±ola (in order to create the lexicon) and the Spanish Wikipedia (for the plain text corpus).

The creation of this software was supported by the Spanish Ministry of Education, Culture and Sport via a doctoral grant to IvÃ¡n Arias RodrÃ­guez (FPU16/04039). It has also been funded by research projects TIN2014-52010-R (RedR+Human) and TIN2017-88092 R (CetrO+Spec).

